---
import QuizLayout from '../../../../layouts/QuizLayout.astro';
---

<QuizLayout
  title="Your Result: The Evaluator — Apron Belly Guide"
  description="You're ready for an honest surgical comparison. Here's what the evidence shows — without a financial stake in the outcome."
>

<style is:global>
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }

.res-wrap {
  max-width: 680px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 1.25rem 5rem;
}
.res-header {
  padding: 2rem 1.25rem 0;
  max-width: 680px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
}
.res-logo {
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  color: #2D2A26;
  text-decoration: none;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}
.res-logo:hover { color: #7A9E7E; }

.res-badge {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  background: #EFF6EF;
  border: 1.5px solid #C3D9C4;
  border-radius: 100px;
  padding: 0.35rem 0.9rem;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: #4F7A52;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
}
.res-badge::before { content: '●'; font-size: 0.5rem; color: #7A9E7E; }

h1.res-headline {
  font-size: clamp(1.55rem, 4.5vw, 2.2rem);
  font-weight: 800;
  color: #2D2A26;
  line-height: 1.2;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.res-diag {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: #6B6560;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #EBE7E0;
}
.res-section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.res-section h2 {
  font-size: 0.68rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: #A09890;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
.res-section p { font-size: 0.97rem; color: #4A4540; line-height: 1.75; }

.res-good { background: #F4FAF4; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-left: 3px solid #7A9E7E; }
.res-honest { background: #FAF8F5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-left: 3px solid #D4CFC9; }

.res-protocol {
  margin: 2.5rem 0;
  padding-top: 2.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid #EBE7E0;
}
.res-protocol h2 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #2D2A26;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}
.res-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; }
.res-step { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start; }
.res-step-num {
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: #7A9E7E;
  color: white;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 0.1rem;
}
.res-step-body strong {
  display: block;
  font-size: 0.97rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #2D2A26;
  margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
}
.res-step-body p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #6B6560; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }

.res-ctas {
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  padding-top: 2.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid #EBE7E0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.875rem;
}
.res-cta-primary {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: #7A9E7E;
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  padding: 0.9rem 2rem;
  border-radius: 12px;
  transition: opacity 0.15s, transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 14px rgba(122,158,126,0.32);
  text-align: center;
}
.res-cta-primary:hover {
  opacity: 0.93;
  transform: translateY(-1px);
  box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(122,158,126,0.38);
}
.res-cta-secondary {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: white;
  color: #4A4540;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 0.93rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1.5px solid #E8E4DE;
  transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  text-align: center;
}
.res-cta-secondary:hover { border-color: #7A9E7E; background: #F6FAF6; }
.res-retake {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: #C4BDB6;
}
.res-retake a { color: #A09890; text-decoration: none; }
.res-retake a:hover { color: #7A9E7E; }

@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .res-header { padding: 2rem 2rem 0; }
  .res-wrap { padding: 0 2rem 5rem; }
}
</style>

<header class="res-header">
  <a href="/" class="res-logo">Apron Belly Guide</a>
</header>

<main class="res-wrap">
  <p class="res-badge">Your Profile: The Evaluator</p>
  <h1 class="res-headline">You're Ready for an Honest Surgical Comparison — Here It Is</h1>
  <p class="res-diag">You've moved past the "should I even consider this?" phase. You want objective information about what surgery actually involves, when it's the right answer, and what non-surgical approaches can and can't do at this point.</p>

  <div class="res-section">
    <h2>What your answers show</h2>
    <p>Based on your situation, you're at the point where understanding the surgical decision clearly is the right next step — not because surgery is necessarily right for you, but because you deserve an honest comparison that isn't being made by someone who has a financial stake in the outcome. That's what we try to provide.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="res-section res-good">
    <h2>The good news</h2>
    <p>The decision between surgery and non-surgery is more nuanced than most sources admit. Panniculectomy is sometimes covered by insurance when functional problems are documented. The criteria are specific and knowable. And there are legitimate cases where non-surgical approaches, used seriously over 12–24 months, produce outcomes that make surgery unnecessary.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="res-section res-honest" style="margin-top:1rem;">
    <h2>The honest part</h2>
    <p>For significant structural loose skin after major weight loss — the kind that causes functional problems, has been present for many years, or involves a large hanging pannus — surgery is the only intervention that definitively removes the excess skin. Non-surgical approaches improve the situation; they don't replicate a panniculectomy.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="res-protocol">
    <h2>Your next steps — in priority order</h2>
    <div class="res-steps">
      <div class="res-step">
        <div class="res-step-num">1</div>
        <div class="res-step-body">
          <strong>Get the honest surgical comparison first</strong>
          <p>Understand the difference between a tummy tuck and a panniculectomy, when insurance covers the latter, and what recovery involves. Decision-making without this information is just anxiety dressed as research.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="res-step">
        <div class="res-step-num">2</div>
        <div class="res-step-body">
          <strong>Document any functional problems now</strong>
          <p>If you experience skin infections, hygiene challenges, or mobility issues related to the pannus, start documenting these with your primary care provider. This is the foundation of an insurance coverage case — and it's worth starting regardless of your final decision.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="res-step">
        <div class="res-step-num">3</div>
        <div class="res-step-body">
          <strong>Continue non-surgical support in the meantime</strong>
          <p>Even if surgery is the eventual answer, collagen, compression, and skin quality work in the meantime. And some people who commit to a serious 12-month non-surgical protocol find the outcome changes their surgical calculus entirely.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="res-ctas">
    <a href="/surgery/panniculectomy-cost/" class="res-cta-primary">Panniculectomy: Costs, Insurance, and What to Expect →</a>
    <a href="/non-surgical-solutions/" class="res-cta-secondary">Non-Surgical Options: What the Evidence Shows</a>
  </div>

  <p class="res-retake">Not quite right? <a href="/quiz/">Retake the assessment</a></p>
</main>

</QuizLayout>
